--- Phase A: Enhanced Match Finding ---

Change 1: Increased hash chain depth 256 -> 1024
  - More candidates examined per position
  - Finds better matches at cost of compression speed

Change 2: Expanded match candidates from 3 to 5 per position
  - Added: best mid-offset match (256<=off<65536)
  - Added: longest match of any type
  - DP optimal parser now has more options at each position
  - match_find returns up to ZXL_MAX_CANDIDATES=5 distinct matches
  - Flat match_all array replaces separate match_arr/match_arr2/match_arr3

Results after Phase A:
  ntdll.dll:   0.4440 -> 0.4418 (-0.0022)  1114133 bytes
  kernel32.dll: 0.4421 -> 0.4409 (-0.0012)  368693 bytes
  user32.dll:  0.3646 -> 0.3637 (-0.0009)  681390 bytes

Compression speed: ~0.1-0.2 MB/s (slower due to deeper chains, acceptable for max compression)
Decompression speed: unchanged ~120-140 MB/s
